Electrum-VIOR - lightweight Viorcoin client

Licence: GNU GPL v3
Author: Thomas Voegtlin
Language: Python
Homepage: https://electrum.viorcoin.com/


1. GETTING STARTED
------------------

To run Electrum from this directory, just do:

  ./electrum-vior

If you install Electrum on your system, you can run it from any
directory:

  sudo python setup.py install
  electrum-vior


To start Electrum from your web browser, see
http://electrum.ciorcoin.com/viorcoin_URIs.html



2. HOW OFFICIAL PACKAGES ARE CREATED
------------------------------------

python mki18n.py
pyrcc4 icons.qrc -o gui/qt/icons_rc.py
python setup.py sdist --format=zip,gztar

On Mac OS X:

  # On port based installs
  sudo python setup-release.py py2app

  # On brew installs
  ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386 -arch x86_64" sudo python setup-release.py py2app --includes sip

  sudo hdiutil create -fs HFS+ -volname "Electrum-VIOR" -srcfolder dist/Electrum-VIOR.app dist/electrum-vior-VERSION-macosx.dmg


